          <title>
            <string language="en">All You Need Is (the Summer of) Love - Creating an Exhibit that Compares 1960s and Contemporary Culture</string>
            <string language="x-mt-de">Alle, die Sie benötigen, ist (der Sommer von) 
Liebe - eine Ausstellung erstellend, die sechziger Jahre und 
zeitgenössische Kultur vergleicht</string>
            <string language="x-mt-fr">Tout que vous avez besoin est (l'été de) amour -
créant un objet exposé qui compare les années 60 et la culture 
contemporaine</string>
            <string language="x-mt-pt">Tudo que você necessita é (o verão de) amor - 
criando uma exibição que compare 1960s e a cultura contemporary</string>
            <string language="x-mt-it">Tutto che abbiate bisogno di è (estate di) amore 
- creando un'esposizione che confronta gli anni 60 e la coltura 
contemporanea</string>
            <string language="x-mt-el">Όλοι εσείς χρειάζονται είναι (το καλοκαίρι) αγάπη - 
δημιουργώντας ένα έκθεμα που συγκρίνει τη δεκαετία του '60 και το
σύγχρονο πολιτισμό</string>
            <string language="x-mt-es">Todo lo que usted necesita es (el verano de) amor 
- creando un objeto expuesto que compare los años 60 y la cultura 
contemporánea</string>
          </title>
          <description>
            <string language="en">In this lesson, students explore various aspects of the 1960s, including the 1967 "Summer of Love," and compare them with contemporary times to ascertain cultural influences.</string>
          </description>
          <keyword>
            <string language="en">Humanities</string>
          </keyword>
          <keyword>
            <string language="en">Social Sciences</string>
          </keyword>
          <coverage>
            <string language="en">North America</string>
          </coverage>
          <language>en</language>
          <description>
            <string language="x-mt-de">In dieser Lektion erforschen Kursteilnehmer 
verschiedene Aspekte der sechziger Jahre, einschließlich 1967 "Sommer
der Liebe," und vergleichen sie mit zeitgenössischen Zeiten, 
kulturelle Einflüsse zu ermitteln.</string>
          </description>
          <description>
            <string language="x-mt-fr">Dans cette leçon, les étudiants explorent de 
divers aspects des années 60, y compris le 1967 "été de l'amour," 
et les comparent aux périodes contemporaines de s'assurer des 
influences culturelles.</string>
          </description>
          <description>
            <string language="x-mt-pt">Nesta lição, os estudantes exploram vários 
aspectos dos 1960s, including o 1967 "verão do amor," e comparam-nos 
com as épocas contemporary verificar influências cultural.</string>
          </description>
          <description>
            <string language="x-mt-it">In questa lezione, gli allievi esplorano le varie 
funzioni degli anni 60, compreso il 1967 "l'estate di amore," e li 
paragonano ai periodi contemporanei accertare delle influenze 
culturali.</string>
          </description>
          <description>
            <string language="x-mt-el">Σε αυτό το μάθημα, οι σπουδαστές ερευνούν τις 
διάφορες πτυχές της δεκαετίας του '60, συμπεριλαμβανομένου το 
1967 "καλοκαίρι της αγάπης," και τις συγκρίνουν με τους 
σύγχρονους χρόνους να εξακριβωθούν οι πολιτιστικές επιρροές.</string>
          </description>
          <description>
            <string language="x-mt-es">En esta lección, los estudiantes exploran los 
varios aspectos de los años 60, incluyendo el 1967 "verano del amor,"
y los comparan con épocas contemporáneas de comprobar influencias 
culturales.</string>
          </description>
